## Project files

- `PRD.md` — product requirements
- `ARCHITECTURE.md` — system architecture
- `tasks.md` — sprint and roadmap
- `ACCEPTANCE.md` — acceptance criteria (the verify gate)
- `.harness/` — build harness state (memory, decisions, rules)

> Add `.harness/state` to `.gitignore` — it is ephemeral phase state used by the optional statusline, not a decision record.

## Workflow

This project uses [bencium-harness](https://bencium.io). Common commands:

- `/bencium-next` — start next task
- `/bencium-decide "title"` — log an architectural decision
- `/bencium-verify` — run the acceptance gate
- `/bencium-deploy` — verify + deploy + health check
- `/bencium-rollback "reason"` — roll back with logged reason
- `/bencium-feature "desc"` — add a feature to the roadmap
- `/bencium-retro` — postmortem after a failure

